lead_paragraph: Because of an editing error, an article in some editions last Monday about the dramatic Olympic qualifying of the American pole vaulter Jenn Stuczynski described her initial struggles incorrectly. She missed the first two attempts at her opening height, 15 feet 1 inch — not at the “lowest height” for the competition, 13 feet 9 inches.
